Here are the detailed views of the different sections of the architecture diagram, as you requested.

### **1\. The Edge Node: Sensor Data Collection**

This image provides a detailed look at the "Edge Node" of the system. It features the Raspberry Pi equipped with the Sense HAT, which collects real-time data on temperature, humidity, pressure, and inertial measurement (IMU). The Python script running on the Pi then packages this data and streams it to Snowflake using the high-speed Snowpipe Streaming REST API.

![][image1]

### **2\. The Neural Core: Data Processing and Analytics**

This view focuses on the "Neural Core" within Snowflake. The raw sensor data is first staged in JSON/Variant tables. From there, it flows into three powerful modules: **Cortex AI Analytics** for machine learning functions, **Snowflake Intelligence** for building a data graph, and **Cortex Analyst** to enable natural language text-to-SQL queries on the data.

![][image2]

### **3\. The Chief Data Officer: System Oversight**

Finally, here is a close-up of the system's "Chief Data Officer," the cat. This thematic element is presented within its own holographic interface, complete with system status indicators and its primary directive: "Feed the data. Then feed me." This adds a fun, personalized touch to the high-tech diagram.
